From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000008 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: local-loongarch64-adaptation <local@example.invalid>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 21:20:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] crate_universe: allow vendored crates on loongarch64

Reason:
//crate_universe:cargo_bazel is built from rules_rust's checked-in
crate_universe/3rdparty/crates/BUILD.*.bazel files. These generated files
were produced before loongarch64-unknown-linux-gnu was added to the local
rules_rust platform set, so their target_compatible_with selects fall through
to @platforms//:incompatible on a LoongArch64 host.

The first observed failure was @@cui__anyhow-1.0.75//:anyhow, but all vendored
crate BUILD files share the same generated platform allow-list. Add
@rules_rust//rust/platform:loongarch64-unknown-linux-gnu to that allow-list in
each generated vendored crate target.

diff --git a/crate_universe/3rdparty/crates/BUILD.adler-1.0.2.bazel b/crate_universe/3rdparty/crates/BUILD.adler-1.0.2.bazel
index 3253ce6fa..ce66701bb 100644
--- a/crate_universe/3rdparty/crates/BUILD.adler-1.0.2.bazel
+++ b/crate_universe/3rdparty/crates/BUILD.adler-1.0.2.bazel
@@ -48,6 +48,7 @@ rust_library(
         "@rules_rust//rust/platform:aarch64-linux-android": [],
         "@rules_rust//rust/platform:aarch64-pc-windows-msvc": [],
         "@rules_rust//rust/platform:aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu": [],
+        "@rules_rust//rust/platform:loongarch64-unknown-linux-gnu": [],
         "@rules_rust//rust/platform:aarch64-unknown-nixos-gnu": [],
         "@rules_rust//rust/platform:aarch64-unknown-nto-qnx710": [],
         "@rules_rust//rust/platform:arm-unknown-linux-gnueabi": [],
